Key Match Events: Max Muncy hit a solo home run and was the only player in the Dodgers lineup with multiple hits.
Freddie Freeman exited the game in the sixth inning due to ankle discomfort.
Post-Match Reflections: Max Muncy expressed disappointment in the team's performance, stating 'We were s--t.'
Muncy believes the Game 2 performance was not indicative of the team's talent, emphasizing their ability to come back from games.
Dodgers manager Dave Roberts mentioned that Freddie Freeman's status remains uncertain for Game 3.
